────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IMPORTANT NOTICE REGARDING CORPUS DATA
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This MIT license applies ONLY to the pipeline source code (src/*.py) and
associated tooling in this repository.

The corpus data — including but not limited to:
  - Original XML localization files (english.loca.xml, ukrainian.loca.xml)
  - Any derived JSONL files containing game text
  - The full parallel corpus (corpus.jsonl)
  - Translation outputs derived from game text (gemini_results.jsonl)

— is NOT part of this repository and is NOT covered by this license.

Baldur's Gate 3 localization text is the intellectual property of
Larian Studios. All rights reserved by Larian Studios.

The corpus was constructed and used solely for academic research purposes
(fair use / fair dealing) as part of a bachelor's thesis at Kyiv National
Taras Shevchenko University, 2026. It is NOT redistributed and is NOT
available for download.

The small example files in examples/ contain 10–20 records per type,
included for illustrative purposes only and do not constitute a
redistributable dataset.

If you wish to reproduce this research, you must obtain the localization
files from a legally acquired copy of Baldur's Gate 3.
